{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Spiced labne","content":["Line simmering basket with nut milk bag or two layers of muslin cloth and set over a large jug or bowl. Place large jug or bowl with lined simmering basket onto mixing bowl lid. Weigh yoghurt into simmering basket. Place into refrigerator to drain for 12 hours. The labne will be soft, yet dense, when ready.","Place a bowl onto mixing bowl lid and weigh dukkah into it. Using a teaspoon, form 12 bite-sized balls from labne and roll each ball in dukkah to coat. Transfer labne balls onto a plate, cover with plastic wrap and place into refrigerator until ready to serve."]},{"title":"Mint vinaigrette","content":["Place all vinaigrette ingredients into mixing bowl and chop <b>20 sec\/speed 8<b>.","Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula, then repeat chopping <b>20 sec\/speed 8<b>. Transfer vinaigrette into a jug and place into refrigerator until ready to serve."]},{"title":"Salad","content":["Place water into mixing bowl. Place Varoma dish into position and weigh pumpkin into it. Rub pumpkin with oil and sprinkle with oregano, secure Varoma lid and steam <b>15 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>.","Insert Varoma tray. Weigh red onion onto Varoma tray, then secure Varoma lid and steam a further <b>2-5 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>.","Check pumpkin and onion are cooked to preference. Secure Varoma lid and steam a further <b>2-5 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>, if needed. Set pumpkin and onion aside to cool for 10 minutes before transferring into refrigerator to cool completely (approx. 30 minutes).","Arrange pumpkin, onion, pomegranate or dried cranberries, rocket and pepita seeds (optional) onto a large platter. Dress with vinaigrette and lightly toss through, then top with reserved labne balls and serve."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Spiced labne","content":["750 g natural yoghurt","150 g dukkah, for coating"]},{"title":"Mint vinaigrette","content":["1 garlic clove","1 ½ lemons, zest only, no white pith","45 - 60 g lemon juice (approx. 1 lemon)","2 - 3 sprigs fresh mint, leaves only, to taste","90 g extra virgin olive oil","1 ½ tsp raw sugar"]},{"title":"Salad","content":["750 g water","675 g Kent pumpkin, unpeeled, cut into thick wedges (1 cm)","1 ½ tsp extra virgin olive oil","1 ½ tsp dried oregano","150 g red onion, cut into wedges (1 cm)","1 pomegranate, arils only","180 g rocket, washed and patted dry","2 - 3 tbsp pepita seeds, to taste (optional)"]}],"id":"r78981","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-noG5Cohsvf8\/XZMv8RE-E2I\/AAAAAAAAaX4\/C4Tw_TosWGQqJlUQC2dMiXknOZzcEentQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_tNrAqf3SqmN9lO8N.png","title":"Spiced labne with pumpkin and rocket salad","publishedAt":"2015-08-07T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"16.6 g","fat":"36.9 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"28.7 g","calories":"2231 kJ \/ 531 kcal"},"usefulItems":"nut milk bag or muslin cloth, plastic wrap, serving platter, large jug or bowl, bowl, plate, jug, refrigerator","hintsAndTricks":["Try making your own <i>Dukkah<\/i> to use in this recipe.","To store extra labne, place into a sealable container, cover with oil and place into the refrigerator.","All elements of this recipe can be made ahead of time and plated just before serving.","Go to the Thermomix in Australia YouTube channel to watch how to easily remove your pomegranate arils in the Thermomix."],"basicInfo":["easy","30m","13h","6 portions"]}